<TITLE>EX-99.1</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 <BODY BGCOLOR="WHITE">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="right"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Exhibit 99.1 </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">


<IMG SRC="g488866g10i15.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="7%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="37%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="54%"></TD></TR>


<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Contacts:</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B>Michael Mitchell (Media)<B></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B>Dexter Congbalay (Investors)</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B>+1-847-943-5678<B></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B>+1-847-943-5454</FONT></TD></TR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="top"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><U><B></B>news@mdlz.com</U></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B></B><U>ir@mdlz.com</U></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>Mondel&#275;z International Highlights Strategies to </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="3"><B>Deliver Sustainable, Profitable Growth at CAGNY </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">BOCA RATON, Fla. &#150; Feb. 19, 2013 &#150; At the Consumer Analyst Group of New York (CAGNY) conference today, executives of Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. (NASDAQ: MDLZ) highlighted the
company&#146;s competitive advantages as a more focused, growth company. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;I&#146;m bullish about our future,&#148; said
Irene Rosenfeld, Chairman and CEO. &#147;Although our top-line growth was disappointing in the back half last year, the quality of underlying revenue and earnings growth provides strong momentum as we enter 2013.&#148; </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Rosenfeld affirmed the company&#146;s 2013 organic revenue growth outlook at the low end of its long-term target of 5 to 7 percent. She
noted that growth will accelerate in the second half as the impact of lower coffee pricing and capacity constraints begin to abate by mid-year. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Multiple Competitive Advantages </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">&#147;We have an advantaged geographic footprint, an enviable portfolio of iconic brands and innovation platforms, a virtuous cycle driving strong underlying operating momentum and a long runway of growth
opportunities,&#148; Rosenfeld said. &#147;As a result, we&#146;re well-positioned for sustainable, profitable growth, and I&#146;m confident in our ability to deliver top-tier financial results.&#148; </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Rosenfeld showcased Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s leading positions in fast-growing categories, with nearly three-quarters of its
net revenue coming from snacks. Globally, the Biscuits and Chocolate categories have each grown 6 percent annually since 2009. Gum and Candy grew 5 percent, while Coffee and Powdered Beverages were up 10 percent and 7 percent, respectively.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">GDP growth per capita in developing markets will continue to be a key driver of these gains. With more than 40 percent of the
company&#146;s sales from developing markets, Mondel&#275;z International is well-positioned to take advantage of this growth. </FONT></P>

<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Rosenfeld also highlighted several ongoing growth opportunities. She cited examples of how
the company is leveraging iconic Power Brands such as <I>Oreo</I> and global innovation platforms like <I>Bubbly</I> chocolate to drive growth. She also discussed how the company is increasing distribution in modern and traditional trade channels as
well as entering white-space markets. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Generating Strong Cash Flow, Returning Cash to Shareholders, Improving ROIC</B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Dave Brearton, Executive Vice President and CFO, provided investors with an update on the company&#146;s cash flow and capital structure.
He said the company expects to generate about $4 billion of free cash flow over the next two years. This will fund the cash impact of the company&#146;s 2012-2014 Restructuring Program as well as cash to pay dividends, leaving approximately $1
billion available for other uses. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Reinvesting in the business to drive growth will continue to be the top priority for cash.
To support this growth, the company plans to increase capital investments to approximately 5 percent of net revenues in 2013 and 2014, focusing on expanding capacity in developing markets. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Even after funding growth opportunities, Brearton noted opportunities to return cash to shareholders through dividend increases and/or
share repurchases. He said the current annual dividend of $0.52 per share will increase over time at a lower rate than EPS growth, but with a dividend payout ratio that would not fall below 30 percent. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In addition, Brearton said that management would ask the board for a multi-year authorization to repurchase shares to offset dilution
from stock options later this year. The cash cost of such a program would be approximately $300-400 million per year. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Brearton underscored that the company would maintain an investment-grade rating with access to A2/P2 commercial paper. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Brearton concluded with a commitment to steady improvement in return on invested capital, targeting an increase of 30 to 50 basis points
per year. Double-digit earnings growth and tight management of working capital and capital expenditures will drive the improvement. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mondel&#275;z International&#146;s presentation was accompanied by slides. Access to a replay of the CAGNY webcast with accompanying slides is available at <U>www.mondelezinternational.com</U>.
</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">2 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>About Mondel&#275;z International </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. (NASDAQ: MDLZ) is a global snacking powerhouse, with 2012 revenue of $35 billion. Creating delicious
moments of joy in 165 countries, Mondel&#275;z International is a world leader in chocolate, biscuits, gum, candy, coffee and powdered beverages, with billion-dollar brands such as <I>Cadbury</I>,<I> Cadbury Dairy Milk</I> and <I>Milka</I>
chocolate, <I>Jacobs</I> coffee, <I>LU</I>, <I>Nabisco</I> and <I>Oreo</I> biscuits, <I>Tang</I> powdered beverages and <I>Trident</I> gum. Mondel&#275;z International is a proud member of the Standard and Poor&#146;s 500, NASDAQ 100 and Dow Jones
Sustainability Index. Visit <U>www.mondelezinternational.com</U> and <U>www.facebook.com/mondelezinternational</U>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Forward-Looking
Statements </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">This press release contains a number of forward-looking statements. Words, and variations of words such as
&#147;deliver,&#148; &#147;affirmed,&#148; &#147;will,&#148; &#147;expects,&#148; &#147;priority,&#148; &#147;plans,&#148; &#147;commitment&#148; and similar expressions are intended to identify our forward-looking statements, including but not
limited to, statements that we are bullish about the future; strong momentum as we enter 2013; 2013 organic revenue growth; second half growth; competitive advantages; sustainable, profitable growth; top-tier financial results; GDP growth per capita
in developing markets; ongoing growth opportunities; modern and traditional trade channels and white space; cash flow; priorities for cash; plans for capital investments; dividends; share repurchase plans; investment grade ratings; and steady
improvement in return on invested capital. These forward-looking statements are subject to a number of risks and uncertainties, many of which are beyond our control, which could cause our actual results to differ materially from those indicated in
our forward-looking statements. Such factors include, but are not limited to, increased competition, continued volatility in input costs, pricing actions, continued weakness in economic conditions, risks from operating globally and tax law changes.
Please also see our risk factors, as they may be amended from time to time, set forth in our filings with the SEC, including our most recently filed Annual Report on Form 10-K and subsequent reports on Forms 10-Q and 8-K. Mondel&#275;z International
disclaims and does not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statement in this press release, except as required by applicable law or regulation. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center">

<tr>
<td nowrap>
<tr>
<td nowrap> <div style='position:absolute;left:27px;top:46px'>

$48 million was recorded in Cost of Sales and $597 million was recorded in Selling, General and Administrative&nbsp; </div>
<div style='position:absolute;left:116px;top:400px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;font-size:12px;font-family:arial,"times new roman",times,serif;color:#000000;'>expenses.</div>
